<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="317" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">884.001 Selassie I/370:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the Emperor of Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Haile Selassie
                                    I</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-20">May 20, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I have received Your Majesty’s message informing me of your return to
                                Addis Ababa, and I assure you of the satisfaction with which I have
                                received these tidings. On behalf of the people and Government of
                                the United States I have great pleasure in extending to Your Majesty
                                my most sincere felicitations on this notable occasion and my best
                                wishes for Your Majesty’s health and happiness.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>